WEBVTT

00:04.880 --> 00:06.880
Hello, dear colleagues.

00:06.880 --> 00:13.280
Today's part of our video course on operational management

00:13.280 --> 00:16.280
will be conducted by me.

00:16.280 --> 00:20.280
My name is Oleg Levyakov.

00:20.280 --> 00:26.280
Today we will talk about several extremely important issues

00:26.560 --> 00:31.560
that are important for the survival of a company in modern market conditions.

00:37.560 --> 00:43.560
One of these issues is the placement of production and service facilities.

00:43.560 --> 00:49.560
Issues such as where to place a factory or enterprise,

00:49.840 --> 00:56.840
where to place an office or a reception center that provides services to the population,

00:56.840 --> 01:02.840
are becoming the main strategies of both production and service companies,

01:02.840 --> 01:08.840
especially in the modern times of global markets and global production.

01:08.840 --> 01:15.840
The drastic changes in trade relations have turned the world into a global village

01:16.120 --> 01:21.120
and have given companies both large and medium-sized

01:21.120 --> 01:26.120
a greater flexibility in choosing their facilities.

01:27.120 --> 01:32.120
However, the issue of practical placement of enterprises

01:32.120 --> 01:36.120
should be solved taking into account two contradictory conditions.

01:36.120 --> 01:39.120
Please look at the slide.

01:39.120 --> 01:45.120
On the one hand, production must be placed close to the consumers,

01:45.400 --> 01:49.400
which is due to competition for time gain,

01:49.400 --> 01:55.400
as well as various trade agreements and the desire to reduce transport costs.

01:56.400 --> 02:01.400
On the other hand, production must be placed close to a cheap

02:01.400 --> 02:05.400
and at the same time highly qualified workforce.

02:08.400 --> 02:12.400
When placing production and service facilities,

02:12.680 --> 02:15.680
companies must be guided by various criteria,

02:15.680 --> 02:19.680
determined by the requirements of market competition.

02:20.680 --> 02:24.680
Let's briefly comment on these main criteria

02:24.680 --> 02:30.680
that affect the choice of the location of production facilities and other facilities,

02:30.680 --> 02:33.680
both service and logistics.

02:34.680 --> 02:37.680
Please look at the next slide.

02:37.960 --> 02:42.960
These criteria are proximity to the consumer.

02:43.960 --> 02:49.960
On the other hand, a very important criterion is the business climate as a whole.

02:50.960 --> 02:53.960
A business climate favorable for a company can include

02:53.960 --> 02:57.960
a comparable scale of entrepreneurship,

02:57.960 --> 03:00.960
the presence of companies operating in the same industry,

03:00.960 --> 03:06.960
in the case of foreign branches, the presence of other foreign companies.

03:07.240 --> 03:10.240
In addition, a business climate is determined by the presence of

03:10.240 --> 03:15.240
a clear and transparent legislation in the business sphere,

03:15.240 --> 03:20.240
the support of entrepreneurial activity by local authorities,

03:20.240 --> 03:26.240
state authorities, subsidies, benefits, and so on.

03:27.240 --> 03:32.240
In total, the last element is determined by the term goodwill,

03:32.240 --> 03:34.240
that is, non-material assets.

03:34.520 --> 03:38.520
The next important criterion is the total costs.

03:39.520 --> 03:43.520
The goal of the optimal location is to choose a place

03:43.520 --> 03:46.520
with the lowest total costs for the company.

03:46.520 --> 03:51.520
In addition to production, they include various regional costs,

03:51.520 --> 03:56.520
internal and external costs for the distribution of goods.

03:56.520 --> 04:00.520
Regional costs include land rental costs,

04:00.800 --> 04:06.800
construction costs, payment of local labor,

04:06.800 --> 04:13.800
local and state taxes, as well as energy and other costs.

04:14.800 --> 04:19.800
There are also hidden costs that are difficult to take into account.

04:19.800 --> 04:25.800
These include costs for transportation to long distances of raw materials.

04:26.080 --> 04:30.080
There are also costs for the transportation of finished products

04:30.080 --> 04:34.080
between various intermediaries up to the end consumer,

04:34.080 --> 04:38.080
which depends on the distribution system used by the company.

04:39.080 --> 04:43.080
It is necessary to consider the weakening of the consumer's response

04:43.080 --> 04:46.080
in the case of a remote location of the consumer market,

04:46.080 --> 04:52.080
which is an extremely important factor in the conditions of the consumer's dictatorship

04:52.080 --> 04:54.080
on almost any market.

04:54.360 --> 04:58.360
The next important criterion is infrastructure.

04:59.360 --> 05:05.360
For any modern enterprise, especially in the field of mass production,

05:05.360 --> 05:09.360
it is necessary to have a well-developed transport system,

05:09.360 --> 05:13.360
including automotive, railway, water, aviation transport,

05:13.360 --> 05:20.360
as well as the provision of electricity needs in telecommunications and communications.

05:20.640 --> 05:28.640
In many countries, the first place is given to the quality of professional training of the workforce.

05:29.640 --> 05:36.640
Educational and professional levels of the workforce should meet the needs of the company,

05:36.640 --> 05:43.640
and even more important is the readiness and ability of the workforce to train and adapt.

05:43.920 --> 05:47.920
The next important criterion is the proximity to suppliers.

05:47.920 --> 05:52.920
The presence of a highly professional and competitive network of suppliers

05:52.920 --> 05:57.920
is one of the determining conditions for the placement of individual units of the enterprise.

05:58.920 --> 06:02.920
The proximity of the main suppliers, among other advantages,

06:02.920 --> 06:06.920
allows the use of methods of organization of the safe production,

06:07.200 --> 06:09.200
the so-called lean production,

06:09.200 --> 06:18.200
or the production of elements in a just-in-time sequence.

06:19.200 --> 06:24.200
It is important to note the role of the location of other companies' facilities,

06:24.200 --> 06:27.200
primarily the management facilities.

06:28.200 --> 06:32.200
The location of factories and distribution centers of the company

06:32.480 --> 06:36.480
can significantly affect the choice of the location of a new facility.

06:36.480 --> 06:42.480
In this context, the decision on the placement is closely related to the choice of assortment

06:42.480 --> 06:45.480
and the volume of produced products for a particular market.

06:46.480 --> 06:55.480
In the conditions of globalization, it is very important to pay attention to the placement of free trade zones.

06:55.760 --> 07:03.760
The so-called free trade zones are usually closed regions

07:03.760 --> 07:07.760
under the supervision of state customs services,

07:07.760 --> 07:11.760
where imported goods of foreign production are sold directly,

07:11.760 --> 07:15.760
without the formalities required by the customs of a particular country.

07:16.760 --> 07:23.760
In free trade zones, producers can easily import imported materials and accessories

07:24.040 --> 07:26.040
used in their own production,

07:26.040 --> 07:31.040
and also receive a delay in the payment of customs fees

07:31.040 --> 07:35.040
until the delivery of the produced goods to the consumer country.

07:37.040 --> 07:42.040
In some countries, especially in conditions when the production capacity of many companies

07:42.040 --> 07:44.040
is transferred to third world countries,

07:45.040 --> 07:48.040
there is a criteria called political risk.

07:48.320 --> 07:53.320
The rapidly changing geopolitical situation in many countries

07:53.320 --> 07:56.320
opens up new opportunities,

07:57.320 --> 08:02.320
but on the other hand, it determines many conditions of risk management.

08:03.320 --> 08:11.320
No matter how promising the idea of placing some production in Afghanistan may seem,

08:11.600 --> 08:21.600
the political risks are such that any company must measure many times before cutting.

08:22.600 --> 08:31.600
This criterion is closely related to the criterion of the presence or absence of state barriers to protect its market.

08:31.600 --> 08:38.600
At present, in many countries, barriers to the entry into the industry and the placement of production have been legally removed.

08:38.880 --> 08:49.880
However, when planning a placement, many not only official, but also legal and cultural barriers should be taken into account.

08:49.880 --> 08:52.880
That is, the difference, first of all, in the national mentality.

08:53.880 --> 09:00.880
The presence or absence of trade unions in one region or another also plays an important role.

09:01.160 --> 09:03.160
What is a trade union?

09:03.160 --> 09:10.160
This is a group of countries that have concluded agreements on mutual conditions of trade in goods.

09:10.160 --> 09:15.160
Companies that place their enterprises within the countries of a particular trade union

09:15.160 --> 09:22.160
use some additional advantages in new markets and provide lower costs.

09:22.440 --> 09:30.440
Recently, when placing, first of all, harmful products, such as chemical, industrial,

09:30.440 --> 09:34.440
as in many industries, color and black metallurgy,

09:34.440 --> 09:37.440
environmental requirements should be taken into account,

09:37.440 --> 09:44.440
which are issued to the companies that are placed, the government of certain countries or regions.

09:44.720 --> 09:52.720
It is very important to consider the interest of the consumer country in the placement of a foreign enterprise in its territory.

09:52.720 --> 10:00.720
At the same time, the significant importance is not only the will of the leadership of a particular state,

10:00.720 --> 10:09.720
but also the educational level of the local population, its quality of life and its attitude to foreign employees.

10:10.000 --> 10:16.000
And the last thing to say is the competitive advantage,

10:16.000 --> 10:22.000
which is extremely important for transnational companies in the matter of choosing a state

10:22.000 --> 10:27.000
in which to place a headquarters or a holding company.

10:27.000 --> 10:33.000
One of the gurus of scientific management, Michael Porter, noted that companies can have

10:33.000 --> 10:38.000
different basic foundations for certain types or parts of a business.

10:38.280 --> 10:43.280
However, the competitive advantage is created in the company's headquarters,

10:43.280 --> 10:50.280
where a strategy is determined, the main product is developed, the so-called product design,

10:50.280 --> 10:56.280
where technological processes are developed, process design,

10:56.280 --> 11:00.280
where the main critical mass of production is created.

11:00.280 --> 11:06.280
Therefore, the company should transfer its basic foundation only to the country

11:06.560 --> 11:13.560
which will encourage innovative activity and provide the best conditions for global competitiveness.

11:13.560 --> 11:28.560
Now, dear colleagues, we will consider the methods used to analyze the conditions for the placement of an object in a particular company.

11:28.840 --> 11:35.840
When performing analysis, the rating system factor is used, the linear programming method

11:35.840 --> 11:40.840
and the so-called centroid method or the center of gravity method.

11:40.840 --> 11:50.840
Each of these methods is a technical tool, and it should be used together with the most detailed and detailed analysis of costs.

11:50.840 --> 11:57.840
And, of course, they should all be associated with the business strategy and business planning of the company's activities.

11:58.120 --> 12:00.120
Please look at the following slide.

12:00.120 --> 12:08.120
The rating system factor is the most widely used general method of location selection.

12:08.120 --> 12:15.120
It is built on a mechanism that allows you to combine various factors in an easy-to-understand and understandable form.

12:15.120 --> 12:23.120
For example, for a certain oil-recycling enterprise, the following score scale is determined in points,

12:23.400 --> 12:27.400
the main factors that affect the location selection.

12:28.400 --> 12:36.400
As you can see on the slide, this factor includes the region's infrastructure capabilities,

12:36.400 --> 12:44.400
the availability and reliability of labor resources, living conditions, the availability of transport networks and some other conditions.

12:44.680 --> 12:50.680
This factor is used to determine the appropriate score scales that you are free to choose.

12:50.680 --> 12:58.680
You need to evaluate each factor in points for each possible location option of this plant.

12:58.680 --> 13:09.680
The overall score of the points is determined by the resulting score, which is the so-called rating of the appropriate location option.

13:09.960 --> 13:17.960
The final location of the plant is chosen according to the option with the highest rating, i.e. the highest score.

13:17.960 --> 13:20.960
However, this method has its drawbacks.

13:20.960 --> 13:29.960
The main problem of using simple rating system factors, i.e. those systems that can be used using paper and pencil,

13:29.960 --> 13:36.960
is that they do not take into account the range of ranges and costs that may take place within each factor.

13:37.240 --> 13:43.240
The first factor may have the highest score, but be unuseful for decision-making on location.

13:43.240 --> 13:48.240
The second may, on the contrary, have a small scale, but determine the real value of the site.

13:48.240 --> 13:55.240
To solve this problem, it is proposed to additionally introduce a weighted assessment of the importance of each factor,

13:55.240 --> 14:05.240
based on relative limits of the cost variation, and not just on the total costs for one or another option.

14:05.520 --> 14:11.520
The next technical method is called the transport method of linear programming.

14:11.520 --> 14:20.520
Those of you, dear listeners, who have basic mathematical or technical training, know what it is.

14:20.520 --> 14:26.520
The transport method is a variety of linear programming methods.

14:26.800 --> 14:37.800
It was given this name because it is widely used to solve problems related to the transportation of products from different sources to several possible destination points.

14:37.800 --> 14:42.800
Such tasks usually follow one of two possible goals.

14:43.080 --> 14:51.080
The first goal is to minimize the cost of delivering a certain amount of products to a certain number of destination points,

14:51.080 --> 14:58.080
and to maximize the profit from delivering a certain amount of products to a certain number of destination points.

14:58.080 --> 15:04.080
These are two approaches that define one picture.

15:04.360 --> 15:12.360
If a creative approach is provided, it can be used to solve different types of tasks.

15:12.360 --> 15:20.360
For example, this method can be used to test the cost of different options of location of new objects

15:20.360 --> 15:26.360
in the existing distribution network.

15:26.640 --> 15:41.640
To do this, you need to add a new line to the table, which must contain the costs of transporting one cargo unit from the producing object to some new place.

15:41.640 --> 15:49.640
Then, a solution is calculated for a new matrix, which shows the minimum total costs.

15:49.640 --> 15:54.640
This is another view that will allow you to make the right decision.

15:54.920 --> 16:03.920
The centroid method is used to determine the location of new objects,

16:03.920 --> 16:08.920
primarily logistic objects, namely, warehouse infrastructure.

16:08.920 --> 16:17.920
It allows to determine the location of an object that provides the minimum costs for transporting cargo

16:17.920 --> 16:23.920
and takes into account the location of existing objects in the production or distribution network.

16:24.200 --> 16:29.200
It also calculates the distance between objects and the volume of cargo that needs to be transported.

16:29.200 --> 16:35.200
In a simplified form, this method assumes that all the transport costs in the forward and reverse direction are the same

16:35.200 --> 16:40.200
and does not take into account the losses due to incomplete loading of the transport.

16:40.200 --> 16:45.200
As we can see from the last conditions, it is also not completely objective.

16:45.480 --> 16:53.480
This is just one of several ways to get a general picture of the solution of an important issue.

16:53.480 --> 17:03.480
Dear colleagues, I am not afraid to show myself as a joker, but I must repeat that by choosing the location of your enterprise,

17:03.480 --> 17:14.480
you are making a very serious investment that should provide you with long-term income as a result of your activities in the chosen place.

17:14.760 --> 17:22.760
Therefore, it is necessary to remember that it is quite problematic to change the location you have chosen once.

17:22.760 --> 17:30.760
You end up with a suitcase with a torn handle, which is difficult to throw away and carry.

17:30.760 --> 17:34.760
Therefore, you need to take this issue very seriously.

17:34.760 --> 17:40.760
If you have located your enterprise in a region with a high cost of energy resources,

17:41.040 --> 17:48.040
then even modern strategic management will not justify the advantages you have lost.

17:48.040 --> 18:00.040
It is fair to use labor resources for the strategy, if the employment in the region you have chosen is characterized by a tendency to increase labor payments,

18:00.040 --> 18:08.040
or vice versa, low labor payments, but poor professional training or low labor discipline.

18:08.320 --> 18:11.320
These issues will also need to be solved.

18:11.320 --> 18:18.320
They are considered by a separate scientific direction, which is called organizational modeling.

18:18.320 --> 18:25.320
In addition, it is impossible to forget about non-economic, political factors,

18:25.320 --> 18:37.320
because there are cases when the decision to place an enterprise provided for consideration by local and regional authorities was rejected at the stage of consent.

18:37.600 --> 18:42.600
Or it could cause a storm of protests from the local population.

18:42.600 --> 18:51.600
This is due to additional costs or losses for the company, so they cannot be ignored when making a decision to place an enterprise.

18:52.600 --> 19:02.600
After you choose the most suitable options for you, the time will come when you will need to make a final decision on the location.

19:02.880 --> 19:07.880
To do this, study the situation in the selected regions, analyzing the following factors

19:07.880 --> 19:11.880
1. Consumer purchasing power in the region

19:11.880 --> 19:14.880
2. Compatibility of the image of your company

19:14.880 --> 19:16.880
3. Corporate culture

19:16.880 --> 19:21.880
4. Service level with demographic situation in the region

19:21.880 --> 19:25.880
5. Competition level with local and foreign manufacturers

19:25.880 --> 19:31.880
6. Geographical features of the facilities of your company and the company of competitors

19:32.160 --> 19:35.160
7. Service level of your company's consumers

19:35.160 --> 19:40.160
8. Your competitiveness and your relationship with business partners

19:40.160 --> 19:46.160
In general, you can draw some conclusions and recommendations on the above problems.

19:47.160 --> 19:55.160
Analyze the options for choosing the location of the company at the stage of the technical and economic justification of the business project.

19:55.440 --> 20:01.440
Choose the location of the company based on the location of the raw materials suppliers,

20:01.440 --> 20:06.440
main auxiliary production materials and semi-finished products.

20:07.440 --> 20:11.440
Location of the main consumption centers in relation to the company.

20:12.440 --> 20:19.440
For example, this is a vitally important issue for the manufacturer of fast-growing products.

20:19.720 --> 20:22.720
Consider the infrastructure of the location of the company,

20:22.720 --> 20:25.720
not only from the point of view of the transport network,

20:25.720 --> 20:29.720
but also from the point of view of the financial infrastructure,

20:29.720 --> 20:35.720
which includes banks, insurance, finance, investment companies and other objects.

20:36.720 --> 20:40.720
Evaluate the possibility of replacing materials and consumables in the event that,

20:40.720 --> 20:48.720
when choosing a location, a significant factor is the cost of transporting raw materials from distant regions.

20:49.000 --> 20:53.000
Even if these regions are familiar to you, regions of production.

20:54.000 --> 21:00.000
Determine the costs for production and marketing operations for alternative locations.

21:00.000 --> 21:06.000
Take your choice so that the costs for the produced product are minimal in total,

21:06.000 --> 21:10.000
and not in individual areas.

21:10.280 --> 21:13.280
Take into account the socio-economic aspects,

21:13.280 --> 21:18.280
environmental factors, factors of the national culture of the population.

21:19.280 --> 21:24.280
After you have identified several alternative options, analyze them in more detail.

21:25.280 --> 21:29.280
Also evaluate the following data and the financial risks associated with them,

21:29.280 --> 21:32.280
using the Risk Management levers.

21:33.280 --> 21:34.280
Production costs.

21:34.560 --> 21:35.560
Production costs.

21:36.560 --> 21:41.560
Production costs for marketing operations, both ATL and BTL classes.

21:42.560 --> 21:47.560
Investment costs, including expenses for environmental protection.

21:48.560 --> 21:49.560
Planned income.

21:50.560 --> 21:52.560
Tax level in the subsidy-benefit subsidy,

21:52.560 --> 21:57.560
which is determined by local and federal authorities.

21:59.560 --> 22:02.560
Pure flows of real money, the so-called cash flow.

22:02.840 --> 22:07.840
Analyze and evaluate these aspects not only quantitatively, but also qualitatively.

22:07.840 --> 22:13.840
And draw conclusions regarding the feasibility and life-span of the chosen location,

22:13.840 --> 22:16.840
without forgetting about the suitcase with the torn handle.

22:17.840 --> 22:20.840
When choosing the location of the company,

22:20.840 --> 22:25.840
pay attention to how it will affect your flexibility.

22:26.840 --> 22:31.840
Production is based on various conditions that can change over time.

22:32.840 --> 22:39.840
The life cycle of modern business structures, modern goods, has been so reduced

22:39.840 --> 22:44.840
that it makes sense to prefer a location that allows for greater flexibility

22:44.840 --> 22:48.840
in relation to modifications and changes in the activities of your company,

22:48.840 --> 22:52.840
including activities in the field of the production of a particular product.

22:54.840 --> 22:59.840
Do not forget about the experience and capabilities of your employees,

23:00.120 --> 23:01.120
especially top managers.

23:02.120 --> 23:07.120
Prefer to place your company in regions where you have personal and business connections.

23:07.120 --> 23:09.120
That is the goodwill.

23:10.120 --> 23:17.120
After we have briefly discussed macro-analyzing the placement of your company's objects,

23:17.120 --> 23:19.120
let's talk a little about micro-analyzing.

23:20.120 --> 23:25.120
That is, the placement of individual blocks of your company on a selected site.

23:25.400 --> 23:29.400
You should approach the placement of production units of the company

23:29.400 --> 23:33.400
as well as the location of the company itself

23:33.400 --> 23:38.400
from the point of view of obtaining the maximum result from the company's activities.

23:39.400 --> 23:45.400
The placement of units on a selected site should be carried out in stages.

23:46.400 --> 23:48.400
Approximately in the following order.

23:49.400 --> 23:53.400
1. Placing workshops and other units on the territory of the enterprise.

23:53.680 --> 23:58.680
2. Placing workshops and other units on the territory of the enterprise.

23:58.680 --> 24:01.680
3. Placing workplaces on the territory of the enterprise.

24:02.680 --> 24:05.680
Dear colleagues, please look at the following slide.

24:06.680 --> 24:09.680
The placement of production units of the enterprise should provide

24:09.680 --> 24:13.680
a rational organization of the entire production process.

24:13.680 --> 24:18.680
To do this, the decision to place production units on the territory

24:18.680 --> 24:22.680
must comply with certain rules and principles.

24:22.960 --> 24:24.960
Here are the main ones.

24:24.960 --> 24:29.960
The first condition concerns the placement of workshops on the course of the production process.

24:30.960 --> 24:37.960
It is very important to take into account that the principle of direct accuracy must be ensured.

24:37.960 --> 24:41.960
To ensure this principle, you must place the main workshops

24:41.960 --> 24:45.960
on the territory of the enterprise along the course of the production process

24:45.960 --> 24:50.960
according to the direction of the main internal factory flows.

24:51.240 --> 24:55.240
From the manufacturing workshops and warehouses to the processing workshops,

24:55.240 --> 25:00.240
and from them to the assembly workshops, and from there to the outgoing warehouses.

25:01.240 --> 25:05.240
2. The location of warehouses at the entrance and exit of the enterprise.

25:06.240 --> 25:10.240
The raw materials warehouses should be placed at the entrance of the enterprise

25:10.240 --> 25:13.240
from the side of the access roads for the import of goods,

25:13.240 --> 25:18.240
and the ready-made products warehouses near the assembly workshops at the exit of the enterprise.

25:18.520 --> 25:22.520
3. The location of auxiliary workshops near the consumers.

25:23.520 --> 25:27.520
The auxiliary production units should be placed as close as possible

25:27.520 --> 25:31.520
to the main production units consuming their products,

25:31.520 --> 25:35.520
without violating the main directions of the cargo flows.

25:35.520 --> 25:42.520
4. The placement of production units taking into account the logistical audits.

25:42.800 --> 25:46.800
The main auxiliary production units, warehouses and other units

25:46.800 --> 25:52.800
should be placed in such a way to ensure the shortest path of the material flows,

25:52.800 --> 25:56.800
the shortest run of vehicles during the production process,

25:56.800 --> 26:00.800
avoiding reverse and counter-movement,

26:00.800 --> 26:05.800
excessive crossings and organization of low-loaded routes.

26:06.080 --> 26:14.080
5. The placement of production facilities taking into account the external factors.

26:14.080 --> 26:17.080
Natural, public, technological.

26:17.080 --> 26:23.080
The main auxiliary production units should be placed taking into account

26:23.080 --> 26:28.080
such factors as natural, such as pink winds,

26:28.080 --> 26:32.080
the possibility of natural lighting, natural ventilation,

26:32.360 --> 26:38.360
the compliance of the architectural, construction, sanitary, technical, fire protection and other standards

26:38.360 --> 26:41.360
provided for your enterprise.

26:41.360 --> 26:46.360
6. The possibility of group building of production facilities.

26:46.360 --> 26:51.360
The separate units, which are closely interconnected during the production process,

26:51.360 --> 26:56.360
should be able to be united into clusters, into groups with placement in one building.

26:56.640 --> 27:02.640
7. The possibility of expansion and modification of production structure.

27:02.640 --> 27:07.640
The possibility of flexible change of production programs.

