01:06:04.440 --> 01:06:08.440
Now, dear listeners, we will discuss the following topic,

01:06:08.440 --> 01:06:12.440
namely, what is a production cycle.

01:06:12.440 --> 01:06:16.440
A production cycle is a period of time

01:06:16.440 --> 01:06:20.440
during which all stages of the production process

01:06:20.440 --> 01:06:24.440
pass, from the first production operation

01:06:24.440 --> 01:06:28.440
to the delivery of the finished product to the consumer.

01:06:29.220 --> 01:06:33.220
This period is divided into two parts.

01:06:33.220 --> 01:06:37.220
The working period, during which the work is in the process of production,

01:06:37.220 --> 01:06:41.220
and the time of breaks in this process.

01:06:41.220 --> 01:06:45.220
The working period is the time of technological and non-technological operations.

01:06:45.220 --> 01:06:49.220
The last number is all control and transport operations,

01:06:49.220 --> 01:06:53.220
as well as operations for re-arrangement

01:06:53.220 --> 01:06:57.220
from the moment of the first production operation

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:02.000
to the moment of the delivery of the finished product.

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:06.000
Business practice shows that the reduction of the production cycle

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:10.000
allows enterprises to accelerate the turnover of their funds,

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:14.000
to implement the established plan with minimal costs,

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:18.000
and to produce a part of the turnover.

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:22.000
This is very important, especially for small enterprises.

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:26.000
The experience of successful enterprises shows that

01:07:26.780 --> 01:07:30.780
the reduction of the production cycle

01:07:30.780 --> 01:07:34.780
is one of the most important tasks of a modern organization,

01:07:34.780 --> 01:07:38.780
which is the sole solution that largely depends on the effective

01:07:38.780 --> 01:07:42.780
and profitable work of the entire system as a whole.

