by Ilya Houdra, which we will discuss further.

01:12:53.360 --> 01:12:57.360
In addition to all this, the modern level of scientific and technical progress

01:12:57.360 --> 01:13:01.360
requires compliance with the flexibility of the production organization.

01:13:01.360 --> 01:13:05.360
Not so long ago, the principles of the production organization

01:13:05.360 --> 01:13:09.360
were achieved by the fact that the production of a certain number of products

01:13:10.140 --> 01:13:14.140
should be stable and stable.

01:13:14.140 --> 01:13:18.140
The production should be stable and the equipment should be of a certain type,

01:13:18.140 --> 01:13:22.140
which sometimes did not change for decades.

01:13:22.140 --> 01:13:26.140
In modern conditions, the reduction of the life cycle of any product

01:13:26.140 --> 01:13:30.140
and the rapid renewal of the product should change the technology of production.

01:13:30.140 --> 01:13:34.140
Meanwhile, a rapid change in equipment would cause

01:13:34.140 --> 01:13:38.140
unjustified high costs for the manufacturer.

01:13:38.920 --> 01:13:42.920
The main advantage of the production organization is the flexibility

01:13:42.920 --> 01:13:46.920
of the equipment, which means the rapid re-establishment of the equipment

01:13:46.920 --> 01:13:50.920
for new, sometimes very relatively related to the previous activity of production operations.

01:13:54.920 --> 01:13:58.920
One of the most important principles of the organization

01:13:58.920 --> 01:14:02.920
is also the complexity of production.

01:14:02.920 --> 01:14:06.920
Modern production processes are characterized by constant interaction

01:14:07.700 --> 01:14:11.700
and integration of the main auxiliary processes.

01:14:11.700 --> 01:14:15.700
Therefore, due to the significant lag of automation of the auxiliary production

01:14:15.700 --> 01:14:19.700
compared to the equipment of the main,

01:14:19.700 --> 01:14:23.700
it is necessary to focus your attention on the rational organization of execution

01:14:23.700 --> 01:14:27.700
not only of the main, but also of the auxiliary,

01:14:27.700 --> 01:14:31.700
providing the auxiliary processes of production.

01:14:31.700 --> 01:14:35.700
Although they do not directly bring profits to the enterprise,

01:14:36.480 --> 01:14:40.480
the most organized functioning is impossible

01:14:40.480 --> 01:14:44.480
effective work of the enterprise.

01:14:44.480 --> 01:14:48.480
It should also be noted that in addition to types,

01:14:48.480 --> 01:14:52.480
production differs in three main methods of organization of production processes.

01:14:52.480 --> 01:14:56.480
Consistent, parallel and so-called parallel-consistent.

01:14:56.480 --> 01:15:00.480
With a consistent method, a part in the production process

01:15:00.480 --> 01:15:04.480
goes to each subsequent operation only after the end of processing

01:15:05.260 --> 01:15:09.260
of all parts of the given batch for the previous operation.

01:15:09.260 --> 01:15:13.260
In this case, from operation to operation,

01:15:13.260 --> 01:15:17.260
the entire batch of parts is transported at the same time.

01:15:17.260 --> 01:15:21.260
At the same time, each part lies on each operation,

01:15:21.260 --> 01:15:25.260
first in the waiting of its turn of processing,

01:15:25.260 --> 01:15:29.260
then in the waiting of the completion of processing of all parts of this batch.

01:15:29.260 --> 01:15:33.260
What are the features inherent in the parallel method of production?

01:15:35.260 --> 01:15:39.260
With a parallel method of processing of each part

01:15:39.260 --> 01:15:43.260
for each subsequent operation,

01:15:43.260 --> 01:15:47.260
it begins immediately after the completion of the previous operation,

01:15:47.260 --> 01:15:51.260
regardless of whether the processing of other parts

01:15:51.260 --> 01:15:55.260
for the same operation is completed or not.

01:15:55.260 --> 01:15:59.260
With this method, several units of the same batch

01:15:59.260 --> 01:16:03.260
can be simultaneously processed for different operations.

01:16:04.040 --> 01:16:08.040
In comparison with the same processes performed in sequence.

01:16:08.040 --> 01:16:12.040
This is the significant advantage of the parallel method,

01:16:12.040 --> 01:16:16.040
which allows to reduce the duration of the production process.

01:16:16.040 --> 01:16:20.040
We have already discussed the benefits of this reduction.

01:16:20.040 --> 01:16:24.040
The third method, parallel-consistent,

01:16:24.040 --> 01:16:28.040
is characterized by the fact that the processing process of parts of a given batch

01:16:28.040 --> 01:16:32.040
for each subsequent operation begins earlier

01:16:32.820 --> 01:16:36.820
than that of the previous operation.

01:16:36.820 --> 01:16:40.820
The parts are thus transferred from one operation to another

01:16:40.820 --> 01:16:44.820
by parts of the total batch.

01:16:44.820 --> 01:16:48.820
The accumulation of some amount of parts on previous operations

01:16:48.820 --> 01:16:52.820
before the start of the batch processing on subsequent operations,

01:16:52.820 --> 01:16:56.820
the so-called production delay,

01:16:56.820 --> 01:17:00.820
avoids the occurrence of lags.

01:17:01.600 --> 01:17:05.600
This is the advantage of parallel-consistent methods.

01:17:09.600 --> 01:17:13.600
Based on the above information,

01:17:13.600 --> 01:17:17.600
we can formulate two main goals of production management.

01:17:17.600 --> 01:17:21.600
The first is to satisfy the consumer demand.

01:17:21.600 --> 01:17:25.600
This is a huge topic, which is devoted to marketing,

01:17:25.600 --> 01:17:29.600
logistics, production management,

01:17:30.380 --> 01:17:34.380
as well as the effective processing of resources.

01:17:34.380 --> 01:17:38.380
Not always modern, especially innovative companies

01:17:38.380 --> 01:17:42.380
give enough space in their strategy

01:17:42.380 --> 01:17:46.380
to the second part of the effective processing of resources.

01:17:46.380 --> 01:17:50.380
Many organizations have suffered a crash on the market,

01:17:50.380 --> 01:17:54.380
despite the presence of quite satisfactory indicators,

01:17:54.380 --> 01:17:58.380
satisfied buyers,

01:17:59.160 --> 01:18:03.160
but they have not been able to rationalize the use of resources.

01:18:03.160 --> 01:18:07.160
There are different approaches and methods

01:18:07.160 --> 01:18:11.160
for optimizing the use of raw materials,

01:18:11.160 --> 01:18:15.160
equipment and labor at different types of enterprises.

01:18:15.160 --> 01:18:19.160
However, in all cases,

01:18:19.160 --> 01:18:23.160
the goal of production management is to achieve a balanced and economical use of resources.

01:18:23.160 --> 01:18:27.160
Its solution is extremely difficult.

01:18:27.940 --> 01:18:31.940
It optimizes the use of one resource

01:18:31.940 --> 01:18:35.940
by going to a certain exit to another.

01:18:35.940 --> 01:18:39.940
This is the so-called triple constraint theory.

01:18:43.940 --> 01:18:47.940
There is a certain contradiction between these goals.

01:18:47.940 --> 01:18:51.940
There are two goals of production management.

01:18:51.940 --> 01:18:55.940
Maximization of the output of the production process

01:18:56.720 --> 01:19:00.720
and the satisfaction of the goal create a conflict between them.

01:19:00.720 --> 01:19:04.720
Often, the improvement of one goal leads to the improvement of another.

01:19:04.720 --> 01:19:08.720
All management management decisions should be made

01:19:08.720 --> 01:19:12.720
based on the presence of conflicting goals,

01:19:12.720 --> 01:19:16.720
the awareness of their conflict,

01:19:16.720 --> 01:19:20.720
and the need to achieve a balance between them at all times.

01:19:20.720 --> 01:19:24.720
The task is also complicated by the fact that each of these goals

01:19:25.500 --> 01:19:29.500
