01:35:37.460 --> 01:35:41.460
Here is one of the tools of the organization of production,

01:35:41.460 --> 01:35:45.460
which is called the flow line.

01:35:46.460 --> 01:35:50.460
The flow line is a kind of a set of processing elements,

01:35:51.240 --> 01:35:55.240
which work at a certain pace and time standard for each technological operation.

01:35:58.240 --> 01:36:02.240
The flow line is often a set of products,

01:36:02.240 --> 01:36:06.240
and serves as an example of the organization of the production process oriented on the product.

01:36:08.240 --> 01:36:12.240
Usually, the term flow line implies a multiple repeating process,

01:36:12.240 --> 01:36:16.240
which has separate links,

01:36:17.020 --> 01:36:21.020
for example, a device for transporting materials.

01:36:23.020 --> 01:36:27.020
Flow lines work at a certain pace,

01:36:27.020 --> 01:36:31.020
quite intensively, but at the same time,

01:36:31.020 --> 01:36:35.020
they are available for all operations.

01:36:35.020 --> 01:36:39.020
At the same time, the time standards of each technological operation are the same.

01:36:39.020 --> 01:36:43.020
Some flow lines are just a device for transporting materials,

01:36:43.800 --> 01:36:47.800
while others are distinguished by a special configuration of the flow line.

01:36:47.800 --> 01:36:51.800
This is a conveyor of U-shaped form,

01:36:51.800 --> 01:36:55.800
rectilinear, winding or other types.

01:36:56.800 --> 01:37:00.800
At the same time, the organization of production by the method of the flow line

01:37:02.800 --> 01:37:06.800
implies a very significant and complex operation,

01:37:06.800 --> 01:37:10.800
which is called balancing the flow line.

01:37:11.580 --> 01:37:15.580
Despite the fact that the calendar planning,

01:37:15.580 --> 01:37:19.580
the most important production plan,

01:37:19.580 --> 01:37:23.580
has a primary role in the management of processes,

01:37:23.580 --> 01:37:27.580
often when the production sites are placed,

01:37:27.580 --> 01:37:31.580
it is necessary to balance the flow line.

01:37:31.580 --> 01:37:35.580
The need for balancing occurs when the size or number of workplaces

01:37:35.580 --> 01:37:39.580
on the flow line needs to be changed.

01:37:40.360 --> 01:37:44.360
For various reasons, including a lack of workforce.

01:37:44.360 --> 01:37:48.360
In the most general case, the assembly line is a moving conveyor,

01:37:48.360 --> 01:37:52.360
the work items on which pass through a number of workplaces.

01:37:52.360 --> 01:37:56.360
At each workplace, a certain technological operation is performed on the product.

01:37:58.360 --> 01:38:02.360
The operation performed at each workplace consists of separate elements of the task.

01:38:03.140 --> 01:38:07.140
These are the so-called working units.

01:38:09.140 --> 01:38:13.140
Usually, working units consist of actions and movements,

01:38:13.140 --> 01:38:17.140
which are difficult to subdivide into smaller units.

01:38:17.140 --> 01:38:21.140
The task of balancing the assembly line is to establish such cycles

01:38:21.140 --> 01:38:25.140
at all workplaces,

01:38:25.140 --> 01:38:29.140
so that each worker performs as many elements and tasks,

01:38:29.920 --> 01:38:33.920
as possible during the entire assembly line cycle.

01:38:35.920 --> 01:38:39.920
And so that the free time not occupied by the operation,

01:38:39.920 --> 01:38:43.920
that is, the so-called downtime, was minimal at all workplaces.

01:38:45.920 --> 01:38:49.920
In the following slides, you will see the algorithm of balancing the flow line.

01:38:51.920 --> 01:38:55.920
It should be noted that purely empirically,

01:38:56.700 --> 01:39:00.700
it can be concluded that the longest element or task

01:39:02.700 --> 01:39:06.700
limits the shortest time of the assembly line cycle.

01:39:06.700 --> 01:39:10.700
This is a kind of bottleneck.

01:39:12.700 --> 01:39:16.700
How to expand these bottlenecks, we will see a little later.

01:39:18.700 --> 01:39:22.700
But one of the technological techniques is the splitting of work tasks.

01:39:23.480 --> 01:39:27.480
Since the time of performing the longest task

01:39:27.480 --> 01:39:31.480
becomes the lowest time limit,

01:39:31.480 --> 01:39:35.480
it is necessary to split the task into two or more parts.

01:39:39.480 --> 01:39:43.480
This can be achieved using task splitting methods,

01:39:43.480 --> 01:39:47.480
using parallel workplaces,

01:39:47.480 --> 01:39:51.480
using the labor of more qualified workers,

01:39:52.260 --> 01:39:56.260
or even come to the redesign of the product.

01:39:56.260 --> 01:40:00.260
All these methods are considered in the following slide.

01:40:02.260 --> 01:40:06.260
When balancing the assembly line,

01:40:06.260 --> 01:40:10.260
there is a problem with the joint performance of the elements of the operation with different lengths.

01:40:10.260 --> 01:40:14.260
The technical solution to such problems is achieved

01:40:14.260 --> 01:40:18.260
by the application of flexible and so-called U-shaped assembly line configurations.

01:40:19.040 --> 01:40:23.040
The U-shaped assembly line has several advantages,

01:40:23.040 --> 01:40:27.040
which include the ability to reduce the time for loading and unloading work,

01:40:29.040 --> 01:40:33.040
due to the fact that the places of the input and output of the finished product

01:40:33.040 --> 01:40:37.040
are in the territorial vicinity.

01:40:37.040 --> 01:40:41.040
This line takes up less space, requires fewer staff,

01:40:41.040 --> 01:40:45.040
and makes it easier for the team to work.

01:40:45.820 --> 01:40:49.820
It is worth mentioning the method of balancing the assembly line

01:40:49.820 --> 01:40:53.820
with the mixed sequence of product models.

01:40:53.820 --> 01:40:57.820
This method is used by many industrial companies,

01:40:57.820 --> 01:41:01.820
which have introduced the Just-in-Time system,

01:41:01.820 --> 01:41:05.820
in particular, the founder of this system is Toyota.

01:41:05.820 --> 01:41:09.820
The purpose of such balancing is to satisfy the changing demand

01:41:09.820 --> 01:41:13.820
for various product models and prevent the formation of large stocks.

01:41:14.600 --> 01:41:18.600
We can quote Mr. Yoshihiro Mandon from Toyota Motor,

01:41:18.600 --> 01:41:22.600
which draws attention to the simplicity of this approach.

01:41:26.600 --> 01:41:30.600
Toyota Motor's assembly line is a mixed sequence of models.

01:41:32.600 --> 01:41:36.600
The daily production is calculated by the division of the number of cars

01:41:36.600 --> 01:41:40.600
provided by the monthly production schedule

01:41:41.380 --> 01:41:45.380
and the number of working days per month.

01:41:45.380 --> 01:41:49.380
The order of the assembly of each model is calculated

01:41:49.380 --> 01:41:53.380
and the sequence of their production is determined.

01:41:53.380 --> 01:41:57.380
In order for the different models of cars to be produced in the set time,

01:41:57.380 --> 01:42:01.380
the order of their production is set on the assembly line.

01:42:01.380 --> 01:42:05.380
